<paragraph id="A431EA841E72499873D3F3A50B0D8158" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C7523C2ED7C5CB40CD151F9D2F17CEDF" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Mascarene Islands (probably introduced), Oriental region and South-Eastern part of the Palaearctic region (Fig. 325).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="20371D9BDA54F0C25F6D8EC13353B41F" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="6A08C4FC8B7C6A1E786456D6881D49AF" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E44D2651C732B03ABD216D1F9B00588B" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
This genus is associated with plants in the families 
<taxonomicName id="32BBB9594E44CACB79714F102DC7256D" genus="Verbenaceae" lsidName="Verbenaceae" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="genus">Verbenaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="08B2D44E878FA455FD02865EEB15F8B2" genus="Lamiaceae" lsidName="Lamiaceae" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="genus">Lamiaceae</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="F57378803927993BFBCE85587D64AFD7" author="Jolivet, P" journalOrPublisher="An essay about the relationships between the leaf-beetles and their food-plants. Backhuys Publishers, Leiden" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" title="Host-plants of Chrysomelidae of the World." year="1995">Jolivet and Hawkeswood 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E607ADB81E752EE326C0989EAD7BE589" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="notes">
<paragraph id="31DEC97A80481FF3718AEB264D5F7D46" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="471A3F1233DB2A9FBAB0D997F4AB9F99" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
The Malagasy species initially attributed to this Oriental genus were previously transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4B9AD579A5CC4E06CAC311F8D36A73E3" authority="Jacoby, 1903" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hyphasoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyphasoma" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hyphasoma</taxonomicName>
Jacoby (
<bibRefCitation id="47AD6010D60F63B0DFD73CB4205924BC" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Heikertinger and Csiki 1940</bibRefCitation>
) and then to 
<taxonomicName id="AF80572D69C8420E3A282BEEE7A7FBE7" authority="Clark, 1863" authorityName="Clark" authorityYear="1863" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Physoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Physoma" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Physoma</taxonomicName>
Clark (
<bibRefCitation id="6041ED793826D5215EF4CE2E3F1FA2D9" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<normalizedToken id="2CCBC507E162F0731FACA4E97E7A31A5" originalValue="Bechyné">Bechyne</normalizedToken>
1948a
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="65ED7F25F727DA250689616024D2D4D2" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<normalizedToken id="B91578558C63FCE53699863ECC949BDA" originalValue="Bechyné">Bechyne</normalizedToken>
(1958a)
</bibRefCitation>
reports 
<taxonomicName id="1EE177F8ED5D2B5BEA8AA3258D270F96" authority="Harold, 1877" authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hyphasis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyphasis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hyphasis</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="920D0D25CD97C8E0E960FB7B656C0FA5" authority="Jacoby, 1903" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hyphasoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyphasoma" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hyphasoma</taxonomicName>
) sita (
<bibRefCitation id="0CEC67FF218C0B9D33EADEB88FD2251C" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Maulik 1926</bibRefCitation>
: 158), described from Sri Lanka (= Ceylon), as an introduced species on the Mascarene Islands (Mauritius). We here confirm that this flea beetle genus does occur on the island of Mauritius.
</paragraph>
